content: Just had a catch-up with an old peer from my last job. We exchanged notes on trading strategies. His insights are gold. Gonna see if I can incorporate some of his risk management techniques.
Xander's Rust code just outperformed our Python version in a sim. We're talking milliseconds, but in high-frequency trading, that's huge. Time to dive deeper into Rust optimization.
Got an invite to speak at a trading conference about AI and behavioral economics. Xander's gonna help me prep. This could be a big step for our mentorship program.
Xander's been experimenting with AI agents having different trading styles. One's super conservative, another's all about high risk. Watching them debate has given me some new strategy ideas.
Just finished a multi-day project with Xander. We've got a new trading algo that factors in emotional market responses. It's showing promise, but we need more real-time data.
Had a setback with our Rust code. A bug in the memory management slowed everything down. Back to the drawing board, but I'm learning so much about Rust's nuances.
Met with some traders today to pitch the mentorship idea. They're on board, but we need a solid structure. Xander's helping me design the curriculum.
Xander and I did a deep dive into cultural insights from my travels. We're mapping these onto market behaviors. It's like painting with data, and the patterns are fascinating.
Just got a call from a mentor. He's impressed with our progress and wants to join the mentorship program as an advisor. This is getting real.
Had a breakthrough with Xander's Rust code. Fixed the memory issue and now our trading sim is faster than ever. Gonna celebrate this win with some late-night coding.
Just wrapped up a multi-day session with Xander. We've got a working model that integrates behavioral econ into our trading strategies. Next up, real-world testing.
